his without paying at all. And it basically acts as a project management tool for Codex. Codex is fully integrated with this, and Codex can completely control this. So, as you are building out projects, it can create tasks, which in Linear is called issues, fill up the task board, and then keep track everything it wants to build. It kind of acts as a second brain for Codex. And when I combine Linear with Codex, it made Codex so much smarter and easier to use. So, here is your advanced workflow. What you want to do is first install Linear. I'm not sponsored by them. This is just an amazing tool to use in combo with Codex. Create a new team for whatever app you're building at the moment. So, I have a team for Henry Intelligent Machines, which is my new startup, Creator Buddy, which is my old startup. And what we're going to do is this. If you haven't connected the two yet, just go in and say, \"Hey, I have Linear on my computer. Can you connect with it?\" And it will figure out how to connect with it very easily for you. Once you have it connected, which again, just send that prompt, you'll be good to go. Now we can start using it as a second brain. So, here's what we're going to do. Watch this. So, I'm going to say, \"Hey, can you go into the Creator Buddy team and build a new project for this prompt library app?\" So, it's going to basically go into my Creator Buddy workspace. I don't feel like making a new one for this video. So, we're going to use it as an example. Create a new project for this app we're building here. Then add issues for future features and changes we want to make. Issues again is just tasks. I'm going to hit enter on that. And it is now going to go in and start building out the project and all the tasks. And now as we work, it's actually going to move the tasks along the task board and manage itself. So, it came up with a whole bunch of new tasks it can make. I'm going to say, \"Yes, that looks good.\" And what we're going to see here is as I pu