ex comes out with a monster mega app update, and it beats it. It just beats it. So, 3 days later, I'm saying Codex is better. They The update they just put out is amazing. Now, on the weakness side, there is no Codex mobile app, but I'm hearing from a little birdie, chirp, chirp, chirp in my ear, the Codex mobile app is coming very, very soon. So, better app, we're going to go with Codex at the moment. Let's talk about model. The better model is ChatGPT 5.5. Opus 47 when it came out was amazing. And much like every other Anthropic model, for some reason, as time goes on, basically once you get past the first week of it being out, it gets significantly stupider. It is so frustrating, and it is like clockwork. It happens every single time. And something that frustrates me is they deny it on Twitter. I don't know why. This happens over and over and over again. And then they deny it on Twitter when everyone and their mothers knows it's getting stupider. I can tell you what's happening. It's pretty obvious what's happening and why this keeps happening with Claude. Anthropic simply doesn't have enough compute. Something they prided themselves on very early on, which I thought was very noble at the time, was they didn't go out and mortgage their entire future on compute. They didn't go out and sign $500 billion contracts with Nvidia when they don't even have nearly that much money, which is something OpenAI did. They basically bet not only their future, but the entire global economy's future on compute demands going up. They signed these huge contracts with money they didn't have. I think that safe bet from Claude is now biting them in the butt. They simply do not have enough compute to keep serving Claude at these really intelligent levels. And there's a lot of evidence to support this. There's not only the feel of the models getting worse, there's also limits going down. Limits keep going down. Everyone's experiencing this. Everyone feels like their limits are going faster and faster and faster. They release new tools like Claude designing. You basically can use it twice a week before hitting your limits. On top of that, they took out Claude Code out of the $20 plan. It's a little experiment they were running with people. They started taking out of the $20 plan. Every decision Anthropic's making right now is pointing to the fact that they just do not have enough GPUs. They don't have enough compute. And so, because of this, it is very clear now that 5.5 is the best model. And one thing that ChatGPT does is they don't make the model stupider. The model feels pretty consistently smart from the time they release it to the end of life of it. And it shows that Sam Altman's bet on buying outrageous amounts of compute was the right bet to make cuz not only does the model not get stupider, the limits are a thousand times better, right? So, that's another advantage, way higher limits. You can use this a ton even on the $20 plan. That's probably enough limits for a vast majority of people. You get way higher limits. And what's amazing is, if I don't know if you're in the Twitterverse right now, but they reset the limits basically every day. Anytime they even find the smallest bug, they go ahead. The guy's name is Tibo. He basically just goes, \"Hey, limits reset.\" It's pretty amazing. So, you basically have unlimited usage, not literally, but basically have unlimited usage of ChatGPT, which is awesome. And then, the other strength of Codex is the integrations, right? So, the integrations with, the biggest one being in my opinion, the image gen model. The image gen model is amazing. I use it for so many things for design. I have a design video from a few days ago you should check out where I talk about the image gen model a ton. It really is amazing. But that doesn't mean 5.5's perfect, right? No No app is perfect. Opus still has strengths. What are those strengths? Better UI. It just comes down to it. Claude is still better at UI. The defau