 over both these tools, both Claw Design and the new Chad GBT image model. I'll go over how they work, and I'll go through my new system that allows you to combine the two to make the most beautiful designs ever. If you stick with me until the end of the video, you will become a world-class designer. Now, let's lock in and get into it. Now, for those who don't know, over the last week, both Anthropic and OpenAI released two best-in-class tools. Anthropic released Clawude Design, which we'll go through fully, a really amazing design tool. And then Chad GBT released their new image gen model, their second generation image gen model, which is by far the best image gen model out there. It blows Nano Banana out of the water. But there are some challenges with each, though. There's some ways that both have weaknesses, and when you combine them together, their weaknesses go away, and they're amazing. The main challenge is, and we'll go through building some designs in a second with design and the image genen model, claw design's amazing, but much like all the other anthropic products, it has really low usage limits. A lot of people ran into this where they try to build a couple designs and by the end of the second design they made, their limits were gone and had to wait an entire week. The issue with the image gen model is there's no design tools out of the box with it. It only creates images you ask for. It's not great at building entire design kits, but it's absolutely amazing at generating images. It's also incredibly inexpensive and you can even use it on the free tier. When combined, it solves each other's weaknesses. The issue with claw design is because of its low limits. If you've never designed things before, if you're anything like me, I've never designed anything in my life. I'm very unartic. I stink at all of that. When I went into claw design, I had to experiment a ton. I had to like ask questions, try things like 10 different times. I hit my limits without creating anything amazing. When I started combining it though with Chad GBT's image gen model, amazing things happen. Let me show you how this works. So, with each tool, we're going to go through four stages in this system. By going through all these stages, you'll not only have way better results, incredible professional level designs, but you also save tons of money because you're not going to keep hitting your claw limits over and over again. So, let's start off on the Chad GBT image side. We're going to start with inspiration. By the end of these eight stages, you'll have a fully working design system prototype for an app that's going to look incredible and that's going to match exactly what you want. So, stage one is inspiration. We're going to start off on the Chad GBT image side. Our goal of using this new image gen model with Chad GBT is to come up with a logo and design guidelines. This is going to be the base of everything we use in claw design. This is going to allow it so we don't have to experiment a ton in claw design. This will be great cuz we can move all this over after. And then claw design can spit us out an incredible design system and prototype in one go. No experimentation needed. So we don't have to hit our limits. So to come up with our logo and design guidelines, the first thing we need to do is find inspiration and give it to chat GBT. So we have a starting point. This doesn't need to be perfect. just find some images out there that you enjoy, that you like, that you want to use as inspiration and then we'll start doing some exploration so we can make it our own. My favorite way to find inspiration if you don't know where to start is I just like scrolling X. So I go down X and I just look for images and logos I like. So I'll go down, I'll look at images and logos like, \"Oh, I like this. I like this gradient right here.\" So what I'll do is I'll bookmark this. And what I do is I add it to a visual inspiration folder. So I go there. That's now