ctually do it. I have to sit there and beg on my knees, \"Please, Chat GPT 5.4, do what I tell you to do.\" And it wouldn't do it. It was very smart, but not about that action. 5.5, slightly less chatty. I felt like I was reading a novel every time I would give 5.4 a prompt. I literally would crash out sometimes and say, \"Please, for the love of God, just stop saying so much. Get straight to the point.\" That is not as much of an issue with 5.5. Still a little bit of an issue, not as much of an issue. Better personality. 5.4 was a cold Terminator machine. It did not feel warm to talk to. It was not quite as fun to talk to. 5.5, better personality. Not perfect personality, better personality. And a big one here, it is significantly smarter. It creates excellent, excellent, excellent code. I basically, over the last few days of testing this, have gotten zero bugs out of the code it's written. Zero, zero, zero. So, it is much, much, much smarter, which is amazing to see. Now, these are all big, great improvements, but I'll tell you what, the biggest improvement comes from the experience of using it inside this app I'm showing you here. This is the new Codex desktop app. You need to do yourself a favor. You need to pause this video immediately. You need to go download this. Go download the Codex desktop app because this is incredible. This is where I've spent 95% of my waking moments over the last few days is inside this app. There are 20,000 different features that make it amazing that I'll be going through in this video, but you need to be downloading this immediately. 5.5 with this Codex app is a match made in heaven. It's a beautiful harmony of AI genius. So, here's the plan for the video and here's why you need to buckle in immediately. I'm going to build out a basic app using this Codex app. I'm going to show you how to use it, many the incredible features. Once we got a good feel for the app, we're comfortable with it, we know what it's doing, then we'll go to a