{"type":"message","id":"0cf5600b","parentId":"33bac3bf","timestamp":"2026-04-29T00:03:45.035Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby wants to discuss the Alex Finn videos and what he can learn from them. He's asking where to start. Let me think about what would be most valuable for him given his setup and context.\n\nLooking at his setup from MEMORY.md and TOOLS.md:\n- He already has OpenClaw set up on his MacBook Air\n- He has Claude Opus access\n- He's interested in making money with AI/agents\n- He has a Telegram-based setup\n- Morning brief skill already set up\n\nThe most actionable thing for Bobby would be to help him actually IMPLEMENT the things Alex Finn teaches. Let me think about what's most relevant for him specifically.\n\nKey things Alex Finn emphasizes that Bobby could actually use:\n\n\n1. Memory flush + session memory search settings\n2. Brain dump + expectation setting\n3. The heartbeat cost trap\n4. Reverse prompting\n5. Building tooling\n\nSince Bobby already has OpenClaw running through Telegram on his MacBook Air, he has the foundation in place. The most immediate wins would be those two settings and the brain dump exercise—the cost optimization insight about the heartbeat trap is important too, but the memory and expectation-setting tips are what he'll feel right away. I should probably ask what his main goal is with this first.\n\nActually, let me just lead with the most pressing issue: the heartbeat can silently drain money without him realizing it, then suggest we tackle the quick wins like memory configuration and brain dump to get his OpenClaw instance working at full potential.","thinkingSignature":"cfdf8162c1ab10fe9fd149cefc41900ecb8c45ee38990c0f9082bd33e11d10d9"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nLet me ask you one question first that will determine where we start:\n\n**What do you want to USE OpenClaw for?** Like, what's the main thing you're trying to get out of it?\n\nBecause Alex Finn covers a LOT — from coding to research to business automation to personal productivity. They all have different starting points.\n\nOnce I know what you want OpenClaw doing for you, I can walk you through exactly what to set up based on what Alex teaches. Rather than me just dumping info at you, let's make it actionable for your specific goals.\n\nSo — what's the #1 thing you want OpenClaw helping you with?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":68347,"output":433,"cacheRead":224,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69004,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777421004962,"responseId":"06407dcd69f6765e32831315eaf8a88a"}}
