{"type":"message","id":"a93ed785","parentId":"8a115fc5","timestamp":"2026-04-29T00:04:18.010Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby wants a conversational Q&A style where I ask questions. I like this approach. Let me think about the most important questions to ask in order. Rather than just diving in randomly, I should think about what Alex Finn teaches and what would be most relevant for Bobby.\n\nKey things Alex covers:\n1. What OpenClaw even is\n2. How to set it up\n3. The Brain & Muscles concept (model selection)\n4. Memory configuration\n5. Cost optimization\n6. Getting proactive results (brain dump, expectation setting)\n7. Reverse prompting\n8. Building your own tooling\n9. Multi-agent teams\n10. What it can actually do for you\n\nBut a good Q&A approach would be more like understanding Bobby's goals, current setup, budget, and what he wants to accomplish. \n\nI'll start with one focused question to understand where he is and what he's trying to achieve.\n","thinkingSignature":"d4ab7f7af552973ab517521d00011dbebe7951ee8d5f0f22423bb395fb8d14df"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nAbsolutely, let's do it that way.\n\nHere's my first question:\n\n**Do you currently have OpenClaw installed and running, or are we starting from scratch?**\n\n(Meaning — are you already set up, or do you need me to walk you through getting it installed first?)"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":326,"output":242,"cacheRead":68544,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69112,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777421053709,"responseId":"06407dfe6aab73ba4230800ee4856f22"}}
