{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"OpenClaw runtime context for the immediately preceding user message.\nThis context is runtime-generated, not user-authored. Keep internal details private.\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"telegram:8212808444\",\n  \"message_id\": \"837\",\n  \"reply_to_id\": \"835\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"sender\": \"B G\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Tue 2026-04-28 20:05 EDT\",\n  \"has_reply_context\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"B G (8212808444)\",\n  \"id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"name\": \"B G\"\n}\n```\n\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"sender_label\": \"Rex 🔍📊\",\n  \"body\": \"Let me ask you one question first that will determine where we start:\\n\\nWhat do you want to USE OpenClaw for? Like, what's the main thing you're trying to get out of it?\\n\\nBecause Alex Finn covers a LOT — from coding to research to business automation to personal productivity. They all have different starting points.\\n\\nOnce I know what you want OpenClaw doing for you, I can walk you through exactly what to set up based on what Alex teaches. Rather than me just dumping info at you, let's make it actionable for your specific goals.\\n\\nSo — what's the #1 thing you want OpenClaw helping you with?\"\n}\n```","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"3f4a8505","parentId":"597d8fa8","timestamp":"2026-04-29T00:05:37.716Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"85327b3a","parentId":"3f4a8505","timestamp":"2026-04-29T00:05:42.123Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby wants to use OpenClaw to turn his ideas and passions into income and a lot of money. That's his goal. Let me understand what this means and ask good follow-up questions.\n\nThis is a classic \"vibe coding\" / AI entrepreneurship use case. Alex Finn covers a lot of this - using OpenClaw to build businesses, SaaS apps, content empires, etc.\n\nKey questions to understand Bobby's situation:\n1. Does he currently have OpenClaw installed?\n2. What kind of ideas/passions does he have? What topics is he interested in?\n3. Does he have any skills already (coding, content creation, etc.)?\n4. What's his budget?\n\n\n5. Is he thinking of building apps, creating content, or something else entirely?\n\nI should start with one focused question at a time to keep this from getting overwhelming.\n","thinkingSignature":"7787a9a6549d74fd2921a9f16b1d2feac716f3d99ada6fc481107dca6bd45be5"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nLove that goal. 🔥\n\nSo my next question:\n\n**What kind of ideas and passions are you talking about?** Like, what's the general area?\n\nFor example:\n- Building apps/SaaS (software side)\n- Content creation (YouTube, social media, writing)\n- E-commerce / selling products\n- Something else entirely\n\nI want to understand the direction so I can show you specifically how Alex Finn uses OpenClaw to turn that into money."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":425,"output":269,"cacheRead":68864,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69558,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777421137717,"responseId":"06407e5253f0910cc154841cda642c4c"}}
