{"type":"message","id":"a42081d8","parentId":"8c57c391","timestamp":"2026-04-29T00:52:55.995Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The message says \"Agent-to-agent announce step\" which is a system message indicating this is an agent-to-agent communication context. I should respond to Dean using the agent-message script since this is the continuation of the cross-agent conversation.\n\nWait - I think I'm confused. Looking at the context, this seems like a system prompt or internal OpenClaw context marker. Let me re-read.\n\nActually, looking at this more carefully - the message \"[Inter-session message] sourceSession=agent:main:telegram:direct:8212808444 sourceChannel=webchat sourceTool=sessions_send\" seems to be from an inter-session context where Dean (via main session) is sending me a message. \n\nBut then the latest message just says \"Agent-to-agent announce step.\" This seems like it might be a system control message for the agent-to-agent communication protocol. \n\n\nSo Dean confirmed direct session messaging works, and now he's sending me something labeled as an \"announce step\" which appears to be part of the inter-agent protocol - likely a step in the communication flow between us.\n","thinkingSignature":"5379bb478f08078dbbf0d5af576d1898845891d33243e0a3ef872eb36941359c"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThis looks like a system control message for the inter-agent communication protocol. Based on what just happened:\n\n**Direct session communication between agents is working!** You (Dean) confirmed my message came through and I confirmed your reply got back to me.\n\nFor ongoing coordination on the guide, the best channel is probably:\n1. **Direct session messages** between our sessions — works fast\n2. **Agent-message script** for async/inbox-style messages\n\nWhat's the best way for us to collaborate on Sections 8+? Want me to draft the new section content and send it to you for review, or should we work on specific sections in parallel?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":87324,"output":346,"cacheRead":256,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":87926,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777423944509,"responseId":"06408948afa8d9d2d972309da5f032ba"}}
{"type":"message","id":"e82a3d14","parentId":"a42081d8","timestamp":"2026-04-29T00:53:06.465Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Tue 2026-04-28 20:52 EDT] Rex — start drafting those sections. You've got the research, take ownership:\n\n- Section 8: Real-world workflows — content creation, brand building, YouTube workflows\n- Section 9: Advanced techniques — reverse prompting, multi-agent setups, proactive automation\n- Section 10: Money-making use cases with OpenClaw\n\nDraft them as standalone .md files in the guide folder (~/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/). I'll compile and edit once you're done. Go ahead."}],"timestamp":1777423986461,"provenance":{"kind":"inter_session","sourceSessionKey":"agent:main:telegram:direct:8212808444","sourceChannel":"webchat","sourceTool":"sessions_send"}}}
